#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1097
msgid ""
"SUSE Edge is using <xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/> in order to customize "
"base SUSE Linux Micro OS images.  Follow <xref "
"linkend=\"kubevirt-install\"/> for an air-gapped installation of both "
"KubeVirt and CDI on top of Kubernetes clusters provisioned by EIB."
msgstr ""
"O SUSE Edge usa o <xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/> para personalizar as "
"imagens base do sistema operacional SUSE Linux Micro. Siga a <xref linkend"
"=\"kubevirt-install\"/> para saber sobre a instalação air-gapped tanto do "
"KubeVirt quanto da CDI em clusters Kubernetes provisionados pelo EIB."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1098 l10n/source/edge.xml:4002
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:4137
msgid "System Upgrade Controller"
msgstr "System Upgrade Controller"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1099
msgid ""
"See the <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/rancher/system-upgrade-controller\">System "
"Upgrade Controller documentation</link>."
msgstr ""
"Consulte a <link xl:href="
"\"https://github.com/rancher/system-upgrade-controller\">documentação do "
"System Upgrade Controller</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><blockquote><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1100
msgid ""
"The System Upgrade Controller (SUC) aims to provide a general-purpose, "
"Kubernetes-native upgrade controller (for nodes). It introduces a new CRD, "
"the Plan, for defining any and all of your upgrade policies/requirements. A "
"Plan is an outstanding intent to mutate nodes in your cluster."
msgstr ""
"O System Upgrade Controller (SUC) tem como objetivo oferecer um controlador "
"de upgrade nativo do Kubernetes genérico (para nós). Ele introduz uma nova "
"CRD, o plano, para definir todas as suas políticas/requisitos de upgrade. O "
"plano é uma intenção evidente de mudar nós no cluster."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1101
msgid "How does SUSE Edge use System Upgrade Controller?"
msgstr "Como o SUSE Edge usa o System Upgrade Controller?"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1102
msgid ""
"SUSE Edge uses <literal>SUC</literal> to facilitate various \"Day 2\" "
"operations related to OS and Kubernetes version upgrades on management and "
"downstream clusters."
msgstr ""
"O SUSE Edge usa o <literal>SUC</literal> para facilitar diversas operações "
"de \"dia 2\" relacionadas a upgrades de versão de sistema operacional e "
"Kubernetes em clusters de gerenciamento e downstream."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1103
msgid ""
"\"Day 2\" operations are defined through <literal>SUC Plans</literal>. Based "
"on these plans, <literal>SUC</literal> deploys workloads on each node to "
"execute the respective \"Day 2\" operation."
msgstr ""
"As operações de \"dia 2\" são definidas em <literal>planos do SUC</literal>. "
"Com base nesses planos, o <literal>SUC</literal> implanta as cargas de "
"trabalho em cada nó para executar a respectiva operação de \"dia 2\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1104
msgid ""
"<literal>SUC</literal> is also used within the <xref "
"linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller\"/>. To learn more about the key "
"differences between SUC and the Upgrade Controller, see <xref "
"linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-uc-vs-suc\"/>."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>SUC</literal> também é usado no <xref linkend=\"components-"
"upgrade-controller\"/>. Para saber mais sobre as principais diferenças entre "
"o SUC e o Controller de upgrade, consulte a <xref linkend=\"components-"
"upgrade-controller-uc-vs-suc\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1105
msgid "Installing the System Upgrade Controller"
msgstr "Instalando o System Upgrade Controller"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><important><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1106
msgid ""
"Starting with Rancher <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/rancher/rancher/releases/tag/v2.10.0\">v2.10.0</link>, "
"the <literal>System Upgrade Controller</literal> is installed automatically."
msgstr ""
"A partir do Rancher <link xl:href="
"\"https://github.com/rancher/rancher/releases/tag/v2.10.0\">v2.10.0</link>, "
"o <literal>System Upgrade Controller</literal> é instalado automaticamente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><important><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1107
msgid ""
"Follow the steps below <emphasis role=\"strong\">only</emphasis> if your "
"environment is <emphasis role=\"strong\">not</emphasis> managed by Rancher, "
"or if your Rancher version is lesser than <literal>v2.10.0</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Siga as etapas abaixo <emphasis role=\"strong\">apenas</emphasis> se o seu "
"ambiente <emphasis role=\"strong\">não</emphasis> é gerenciado pelo Rancher, "
"ou se a versão do Rancher é inferior a <literal>v2.10.0</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1108
msgid ""
"We recommend that you install SUC through Fleet (<xref "
"linkend=\"components-fleet\"/>) located in the <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/fleet-examples\">suse-edge/fleet-examples</link> "
"repository."
msgstr ""
