"additional\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1220
msgid ""
"During the upgrade process, the Upgrade Controller continually outputs "
"upgrade information to the created <literal>UpgradePlan</literal>. For more "
"information on how to track the upgrade process, see Tracking the upgrade "
"process (<xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-how-track\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"Durante o processo de upgrade, o Controller de upgrade envia continuamente "
"as informações de upgrade para o <literal>UpgradePlan</literal> criado. Para "
"obter mais informações sobre como acompanhar o processo de upgrade, consulte "
"Acompanhando o processo de upgrade (<xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-"
"controller-how-track\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1221
msgid "Operating System upgrade"
msgstr "Upgrade do sistema operacional"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1222
msgid ""
"To upgrade the operating system, the Upgrade Controller creates SUC (<xref "
"linkend=\"components-system-upgrade-controller\"/>) Plans that have the "
"following naming template:"
msgstr ""
"Para fazer upgrade do sistema operacional, o Controller de upgrade cria "
"planos do SUC (<xref linkend=\"components-system-upgrade-controller\"/>) com "
"o seguinte gabarito de nomenclatura:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1223
msgid ""
"For SUC Plans related to control plane node OS upgrades - "
"<literal>control-plane-&lt;os-name&gt;-&lt;os-version&gt;-&lt;suffix&gt;</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Para planos do SUC relacionados a upgrades de sistema operacional de nó do "
"plano de controle: <literal>control-plane-&lt;nome-do-so&gt;-&lt;versão-do-"
"so&gt;-&lt;sufixo&gt;</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1224
msgid ""
"For SUC Plans related to worker node OS upgrades - "
"<literal>workers-&lt;os-name&gt;-&lt;os-version&gt;-&lt;suffix&gt;</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Para planos do SUC relacionados a upgrades de sistema operacional de nó do "
"worker: <literal>workers-&lt;nome-do-so&gt;-&lt;versão-do-"
"so&gt;-&lt;sufixo&gt;</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1225
msgid ""
"Based on these plans, SUC proceeds to create workloads on each node of the "
"cluster that perform the actual OS upgrade."
msgstr ""
"Com base nesses planos, o SUC cria as cargas de trabalho em cada nó do "
"cluster que faz o upgrade real do sistema operacional."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1226
msgid ""
"Depending on the <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal>, the OS upgrade may "
"include:"
msgstr ""
"Dependendo do <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal>, o upgrade de sistema "
"operacional pode incluir:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1227
msgid ""
"Package only updates - for use-cases where the OS version does not change "
"between Edge releases."
msgstr ""
"Atualizações somente de pacotes: para casos de uso em que a versão do "
"sistema operacional não é alterada entre os lançamentos do Edge."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1228
msgid ""
"Full OS migration - for use-cases where the OS version changes between Edge "
"releases."
msgstr ""
"Migração completa do sistema operacional: para casos de uso em que a versão "
"do sistema operacional é alterada entre os lançamentos do Edge."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1229
msgid ""
"The upgrade is executed <emphasis role=\"strong\">one</emphasis> node at a "
"time starting with the control plane nodes first. Only if the control-plane "
"node upgrade finishes will the worker nodes begin to be upgraded."
msgstr ""
"O upgrade é feito <emphasis role=\"strong\">um</emphasis> nó de cada vez, "
"começando primeiro pelos nós do plano de controle. Apenas quando o upgrade "
"do nó do plano de controle é concluído que o upgrade dos nós do worker é "
"iniciado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1230
msgid ""
"The Upgrade Controller configures the OS SUC Plans to do perform a <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_drain/\">drain</link> "
"of the cluster nodes if the cluster has more than <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">one</emphasis> node of the specified type."
msgstr ""
"O Controller de upgrade configura os planos do SUC de sistema operacional "
"para fazer uma <link xl:href="
"\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_drain/\""
">drenagem</link> dos nós do cluster, se o cluster tiver mais de um <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">um</emphasis> nó do tipo especificado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1231 l10n/source/edge.xml:1240
msgid ""
"For clusters where the control plane nodes are <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">greater than</emphasis> one and there is <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">only one</emphasis> worker node, a drain will be performed "
"only for the control plane nodes and vice versa."
msgstr ""
"Para os clusters em que os nós do plano de controle são <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">mais de</emphasis> um, e existe <emphasis role=\"strong\">apenas "
"um</emphasis> nó do worker, a drenagem será realizada somente para os nós do "
"plano de controle e vice-versa."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1232
msgid ""
"For information on how to disable node drains altogether, see the "
"UpgradePlan (<xref "
"linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-extensions-upgrade-plan\"/>) "
"section."
msgstr ""
"Para obter informações sobre como desabilitar completamente as drenagens de "
"nós, consulte a seção UpgradePlan (<xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-"
"controller-extensions-upgrade-plan\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1233
msgid "Kubernetes upgrade"
msgstr "Upgrade do Kubernetes"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1234
msgid ""
"To upgrade the Kubernetes distribution of a cluster, the Upgrade Controller "
"creates SUC (<xref linkend=\"components-system-upgrade-controller\"/>) Plans "
"that have the following naming template:"
msgstr ""
"Para fazer upgrade da distribuição Kubernetes de um cluster, o Controller de "
"upgrade cria planos do SUC (<xref linkend=\"components-system-upgrade-"
"controller\"/>) com o seguinte gabarito de nomenclatura:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1235
msgid ""
"For SUC Plans related to control plane node Kubernetes upgrades - "
"<literal>control-plane-&lt;k8s-version&gt;-&lt;suffix&gt;</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Para os planos do SUC relacionados a ugrades do Kubernetes em nós do plano "
"de controle: <literal>control-plane-&lt;versão-do-"
"k8s&gt;-&lt;sufixo&gt;</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1236
msgid ""
"For SUC Plans related to worker node Kubernetes upgrades - "
"<literal>workers-&lt;k8s-version&gt;-&lt;suffix&gt;</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Para os planos do SUC relacionados a upgrades do Kubernetes em nós do worker:"
" <literal>workers-&lt;versão-do-k8s&gt;-&lt;sufixo&gt;</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1237
msgid ""
"Based on these plans, SUC proceeds to create workloads on each node of the "
"cluster that perform the actual Kubernetes upgrade."
msgstr ""
"Com base nesses planos, o SUC cria as cargas de trabalho em cada nó do "
"cluster que faz o upgrade real do Kubernetes."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1238
msgid ""
"The Kubernetes upgrade will happen <emphasis role=\"strong\">one</emphasis> "
"node at a time starting with the control plane nodes first. Only if the "
"control plane node upgrade finishes will the worker nodes begin to be "
"upgraded."
msgstr ""
"O upgrade do Kubernetes é feito <emphasis role=\"strong\">um</emphasis> nó "
"de cada vez, começando primeiro pelos nós do plano de controle. Apenas "
"quando o upgrade do nó do plano de controle é concluído que o upgrade dos "
"nós do worker é iniciado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1239
msgid ""
"The Upgrade Controller configures the Kubernetes SUC Plans to perform a "
"<link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_drain/\">drain</link> "
"of the cluster nodes if the cluster has more than <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">one</emphasis> node of the specified type."
msgstr ""
"O Controller de upgrade configura os planos do SUC do Kubernetes para fazer "
"uma <link xl:href="
"\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_drain/\""
">drenagem</link> dos nós do cluster, se o cluster tiver mais de um <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">um</emphasis> nó do tipo especificado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1241
msgid ""
"For information on how to disable node drains altogether, see <xref "
"linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-extensions-upgrade-plan\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Para obter informações sobre como desabilitar completamente as drenagens de "
"nós, consulte a <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-extensions-"
"upgrade-plan\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1242
msgid "Additional components upgrades"
msgstr "Upgrades de componentes adicionais"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1243
msgid ""
"Currently, all additional components are installed via Helm charts. For a "
"full list of the components for a specific release, refer to the Release "
"Notes (<xref linkend=\"release-notes\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"Atualmente, todos os componentes adicionais são instalados por gráficos "
"Helm. Para ver a lista completa dos componentes de uma versão específica, "
"consulte as Notas de lançamento (<xref linkend=\"release-notes\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1244
msgid ""
"For Helm charts deployed through EIB (<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>), "
"the Upgrade Controller updates the existing <link "
"xl:href=\"https://docs.rke2.io/helm#using-the-helm-crd\">HelmChart CR</link> "
"of each component."
msgstr ""
"Para gráficos Helm implantados pelo EIB (<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>)"
", o Controller de upgrade atualiza o <link xl:href="
"\"https://docs.rke2.io/helm#using-the-helm-crd\">HelmChart CR</link> "
"existente de cada componente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1245
msgid ""
"For Helm charts deployed outside of EIB, the Upgrade Controller creates a "
"<literal>HelmChart</literal> resource for each component."
msgstr ""
"Para gráficos Helm implantados fora do EIB, o Controller de upgrade cria um "
"recurso <literal>HelmChart</literal> para cada componente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1246
msgid ""
"After the creation/update of the <literal>HelmChart</literal> resource, the "
"Upgrade Controller relies on the <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/k3s-io/helm-controller/\">helm-controller</link> "
"to pick up this change and proceed with the actual component upgrade."
msgstr ""
"Após a criação/atualização do recurso <literal>HelmChart</literal>, o "
"Controller de upgrade se baseia no <link xl:href="
"\"https://github.com/k3s-io/helm-controller/\">helm-controller</link> para "
"detectar essa alteração e prosseguir com o upgrade real do componente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1247
msgid ""
"Charts will be upgraded sequentially based on their order in the "
"<literal>ReleaseManifest</literal>. Additional values can also be passed "
"through the <literal>UpgradePlan</literal>. If a chart’s version remains "
"unchanged in the new SUSE Edge release, it will not be upgraded. For more "
"information about this, refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-extensions-upgrade-plan\"/>."
msgstr ""
"O upgrade dos gráficos será feito em sequência de acordo com a ordem "
"apresentada no <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal>. É possível também "
"especificar mais valores no <literal>UpgradePlan</literal>. Se uma versão de "
"gráfico permanecer inalterada no novo lançamento do SUSE Edge, o upgrade "
"dele não será feito. Para obter mais informações sobre isso, consulte a "
"<xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-extensions-upgrade-plan\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1248
msgid "Kubernetes API extensions"
msgstr "Extensões de API Kubernetes"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1249
msgid "Extensions to the Kubernetes API introduced by the Upgrade Controller."
msgstr "Extensões para a API Kubernetes lançadas pelo Controller de upgrade."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1250
msgid "UpgradePlan"
msgstr "UpgradePlan"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1251
msgid ""
"The Upgrade Controller introduces a new Kubernetes <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">custom "
"resource</link> called an <literal>UpgradePlan</literal>."
msgstr ""
"O Controller de upgrade lança um novo <link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/"
"docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">recurso "
"personalizado</link> do Kubernetes chamado <literal>UpgradePlan</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1252
msgid ""
"The <literal>UpgradePlan</literal> serves as an instruction mechanism for "
"the Upgrade Controller and it supports the following configurations:"
msgstr ""
"O <literal>UpgradePlan</literal> atua como um mecanismo de instrução para o "
"Controller de upgrade e oferece suporte às seguintes configurações:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1253
msgid ""
"<literal>releaseVersion</literal> - Edge release version to which the "
"cluster should be upgraded to. The release version must follow <link "
"xl:href=\"https://semver.org\">semantic</link> versioning and should be "
"retrieved from the Release Notes (<xref linkend=\"release-notes\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>releaseVersion</literal>: a versão de lançamento do Edge para a "
"qual o upgrade do cluster deve ser feito. Ela deve seguir o controle de "
"versão <link xl:href=\"https://semver.org\">semântico</link> e ser "
"recuperada das Notas de lançamento (<xref linkend=\"release-notes\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1254
msgid ""
"<literal>disableDrain</literal> - <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">Optional</emphasis>; instructs the Upgrade Controller on "
"whether to disable node <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_drain/\">drains</link>. "
"Useful for when you have workloads with <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/run-application/configure-pdb/\">Disruption "
"Budgets</link>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>disableDrain</literal> (<emphasis role=\"strong\""
">opcional</emphasis>): indica se o Controller de upgrade deve ou não "
"desabilitar as <link xl:href="
"\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_drain/\""
">drenagens</link> de nós. Útil quando você tem cargas de trabalho com <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/run-application/configure-pdb/\""
">orçamentos de interrupção</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1255
msgid "Example for control plane node drain disablement:"
msgstr "Exemplo de desabilitação de drenagem de nó do plano de controle:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1256
msgid "Example for control plane and worker node drain disablement:"
msgstr ""
"Exemplo de desabilitação de drenagem de nó do plano de controle e do worker:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1257
msgid ""
"<literal>helm</literal> - <emphasis role=\"strong\">Optional</emphasis>; "
"specifies additional values for components installed via Helm."
msgstr ""
"<literal>helm</literal> (<emphasis role=\"strong\">opcional</emphasis>): "
"especifica valores adicionais para componentes instalados pelo Helm."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><warning><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1258
msgid ""
"It is only advised to use this field for values that are critical for "
"upgrades. Standard chart value updates should be performed after the "
"respective charts have been upgraded to the next version."
msgstr ""
"Somente é aconselhável usar esse campo para valores que sejam críticos aos "
"upgrades. As atualizações nos valores de gráficos padrão deverão ser feitas "
"depois que o upgrade dos respectivos gráficos for feito para a versão "
"seguinte."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1259
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Exemplo:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1260
msgid "ReleaseManifest"
msgstr "ReleaseManifest"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1261
msgid ""
"The Upgrade Controller introduces a new Kubernetes <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">custom "
"resource</link> called a <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal>."
msgstr ""
"O Controller de upgrade lança um novo <link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/"
"docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">recurso "
"personalizado</link> do Kubernetes chamado "
"<literal>ReleaseManifest</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1262
msgid ""
"The <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> resource is created by the Upgrade "
"Controller and holds component data for <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">one</emphasis> specific Edge release version. This means "
"that each Edge release version upgrade will be represented by a different "
"<literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> resource."
msgstr ""
"O recurso <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> é criado pelo Controller de "
"upgrade e armazena os dados de componente referentes a <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">uma</emphasis> versão de lançamento específica do Edge. Isso "
"significa que o upgrade de cada versão de lançamento do Edge será "
"representado por um recurso <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> diferente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><warning><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1263
msgid "The Release Manifest should always be created by the Upgrade Controller."
msgstr "O Controller de upgrade sempre deve criar o ReleaseManifest."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><warning><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1264
msgid ""
"It is not advisable to manually create or edit the "
"<literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> resources. Users that decide to do so "
"should do this <emphasis role=\"strong\">at their own risk</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Não é aconselhável criar manualmente ou editar os recursos "
"<literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> . O usuários que decidirem por esse "
"método devem fazê-lo <emphasis role=\"strong\">por sua conta e "
"risco</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1265
msgid ""
"Component data that the Release Manifest ships include, but is not limited "
"to:"
msgstr ""
"O ReleaseManifest inclui os seguintes dados de componente, mas sem limitação:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1266
msgid ""
"Operating System data - version, supported architectures, additional upgrade "
"data, etc."
msgstr ""
"Dados de sistema operacional: versão, arquiteturas suportadas, dados "
"adicionais de upgrade etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1267
msgid ""
"Kubernetes distribution data - <link "
"xl:href=\"https://docs.rke2.io\">RKE2</link>/<link "
"xl:href=\"https://k3s.io\">K3s</link> supported versions"
msgstr ""
"Dados de distribuição Kubernetes: versões suportadas do <link xl:href="
"\"https://docs.rke2.io\">RKE2</link>/<link xl:href=\"https://k3s.io\""
">K3s</link>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1268
msgid ""
"Additional components data - SUSE Helm chart data (location, version, name, "
"etc.)"
msgstr ""
"Dados de componentes adicionais: dados de gráficos Helm do SUSE (local, "
"versão, nome etc.)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1269
msgid ""
"For an example of how a Release Manifest can look, refer to the <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/upgrade-controller/blob/main/config/samples/lifecycle_v1alpha1_releasemanifest.yaml\">upstream</link> "
"documentation. <emphasis>Please note that this is just an example and it is "
"not intended to be created as a valid <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> "
"resource.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""
"Para ver um exemplo da aparência de um ReleaseManifest, consulte a "
"documentação <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/upgrade-controller/"
"blob/main/config/samples/lifecycle_v1alpha1_releasemanifest.yaml\">upstream</"
"link>. <emphasis>Tenha em mente que se trata apenas de um exemplo, sem a "
"intenção de criar um recurso <literal>ReleaseManifest</literal> "
"válido.</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1270
msgid "Tracking the upgrade process"
msgstr "Acompanhando o processo de upgrade"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1271
msgid ""
"This section serves as means to track and debug the upgrade process that the "
"Upgrade Controller initiates once the user creates an "
"<literal>UpgradePlan</literal> resource."
msgstr ""
"Esta seção apresenta como acompanhar e depurar o processo de upgrade que o "
"Controller de upgrade inicia após a criação do recurso "
"<literal>UpgradePlan</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1272
msgid "General"
msgstr "Geral"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1273
msgid ""
"General information about the state of the upgrade process can be viewed in "
"the Upgrade Plan’s status conditions."
msgstr ""
"Acesse as informações gerais sobre o estado do processo de upgrade em "
"Condições de status do UpgradePlan."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1274
msgid "The Upgrade Plan resource’s status can be viewed in the following way:"
msgstr "Veja o status do recurso UpgradePlan da seguinte maneira:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><formalpara><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1275
msgid "Running Upgrade Plan example:"
msgstr "Exemplo de execução do UpgradePlan:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1276
msgid ""
"Here you can view every component that the Upgrade Controller will try to "
"schedule an upgrade for. Each condition follows the below template:"
msgstr ""
"Aqui você vê todos os componentes para os quais o Controller de upgrade "
"tentará programar um upgrade. Cada condição segue o gabarito abaixo:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1277
msgid ""
"<literal>lastTransitionTime</literal> - the last time that this component "
"condition has transitioned from one status to another."
msgstr ""
"<literal>lastTransitionTime</literal>: a hora em que a condição do "
"componente mudou de um status para outro pela última vez."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1278
msgid ""
"<literal>message</literal> - message that indicates the current upgrade "
"state of the specific component condition."
msgstr ""
"<literal>message</literal>: mensagem que indica o estado atual do upgrade da "
"condição do componente específico."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1279
msgid ""
"<literal>reason</literal> - the current upgrade state of the specific "
"component condition. Possible <literal>reasons</literal> include:"
msgstr ""
"<literal>reason</literal>: o estado atual do upgrade da condição do "
"componente específico. Os possíveis <literal>motivos</literal> incluem:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1280
msgid ""
"<literal>Succeeded</literal> - upgrade of the specific component is "
"successful."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Succeeded</literal>: o upgrade do componente específico foi bem-"
"sucedido."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1281
msgid "<literal>Failed</literal> - upgrade of the specific component has failed."
msgstr "<literal>Failed</literal>: falha no upgrade do componente específico."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1282
msgid ""
"<literal>InProgress</literal> - upgrade of the specific component is "
"currently in progress."
msgstr ""
"<literal>InProgress</literal>: o upgrade do componente específico está em "
"andamento."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1283
msgid ""
"<literal>Pending</literal> - upgrade of the specific component is not yet "
"scheduled."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Pending</literal>: o upgrade do componente específico ainda não foi "
"programado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1284
msgid ""
"<literal>Skipped</literal> - specific component is not found on the cluster, "
"so its upgrade will be skipped."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Skipped</literal>: o componente específico não foi encontrado no "
"cluster, portanto, o upgrade dele será ignorado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1285
msgid ""
"<literal>Error</literal> - specific component has encountered a transient "
"error."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Error</literal>: o componente específico encontrou um erro "
"temporário."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1286
msgid ""
"<literal>status</literal> - status of the current condition "
"<literal>type</literal>, one of <literal>True</literal>, "
"<literal>False</literal>, <literal>Unknown</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>status</literal>: o status do <literal>type</literal> (tipo) da "
"condição atual, que pode ser <literal>True</literal> (Verdadeiro), "
"<literal>False</literal> (Falso) ou <literal>Unknown</literal> "
"(Desconhecido)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1287
msgid "<literal>type</literal> - indicator for the currently upgraded component."
msgstr ""
"<literal>type</literal>: indicador do componente que está passando por "
"upgrade."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1288
msgid ""
"The Upgrade Controller creates SUC Plans for component conditions of type "
"<literal>OSUpgraded</literal> and <literal>KubernetesUpgraded</literal>. To "
"further track the SUC Plans created for these components, refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"components-system-upgrade-controller-monitor-plans\"/>."
msgstr ""
"O Controller de upgrade cria planos do SUC para as condições de componente "
"do tipo <literal>OSUpgraded</literal> e <literal>KubernetesUpgraded</"
"literal>. Para acompanhar em mais detalhes os planos do SUC criados para "
"esses componentes, consulte a <xref linkend=\"components-system-upgrade-"
"controller-monitor-plans\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1289
msgid ""
"All other component condition types can be further tracked by viewing the "
"resources created for them by the <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/k3s-io/helm-controller/\">helm-controller</link>. "
"For more information, see <xref "
"linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-how-track-helm\"/>."
msgstr ""
"É possível acompanhar em mais detalhes todos os outros tipos de condição de "
"componente visualizando os recursos criados para eles pelo <link xl:href="
"\"https://github.com/k3s-io/helm-controller/\">helm-controller</link>. Para "
"obter mais informações, consulte a <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-"
"controller-how-track-helm\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1290
msgid ""
"An Upgrade Plan scheduled by the Upgrade Controller can be marked as "
"<literal>successful</literal> once:"
msgstr ""
"É possível marcar um UpgradePlan programado pelo Controller de upgrade como "
"<literal>successful</literal> (bem-sucedido) se:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1291
msgid ""
"There are no <literal>Pending</literal> or <literal>InProgress</literal> "
