#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1955
msgid ""
"The Kubernetes distribution upgrade for management cluster nodes is done by "
"utilizing <literal>Fleet</literal> and the <literal>System Upgrade "
"Controller (SUC)</literal>."
msgstr ""
"O upgrade de distribuições Kubernetes para nós de cluster de gerenciamento é "
"feito pelo <literal>Fleet</literal> e pelo <literal>System Upgrade "
"Controller (SUC)</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1956 l10n/source/edge.xml:2461
msgid ""
"<literal>Fleet</literal> is used to deploy and manage <literal>SUC "
"plans</literal> onto the desired cluster."
msgstr ""
"O <literal>Fleet</literal> é usado para implantar e gerenciar "
"<literal>planos do SUC</literal> no cluster desejado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1957 l10n/source/edge.xml:2462
msgid ""
"<literal>SUC plans</literal> are <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">custom "
"resources</link> that describe the steps that <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">SUC</emphasis> needs to follow in order for a specific task "
"to be executed on a set of nodes. For an example of how an <literal>SUC "
"plan</literal> looks like, refer to the <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/rancher/system-upgrade-controller?tab=readme-ov-file#example-plans\">upstream "
"repository</link>."
msgstr ""
"Os <literal>planos do SUC</literal> são <link xl:href=\"https://"
"kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/"
"\">recursos personalizados</link> que descrevem as etapas que o <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">SUC</emphasis> precisa seguir para execução de uma tarefa "
"específica em um conjunto de nós. Para ver um exemplo de como é um "
"<literal>plano do SUC</literal>, consulte o <link xl:href=\"https://"
"github.com/rancher/system-upgrade-controller?tab=readme-ov-file#example-"
"plans\">repositório upstream</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1958 l10n/source/edge.xml:2463
msgid ""
"The <literal>K8s SUC plans</literal> are shipped on each cluster by "
"deploying a <link "
"xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/gitrepo-add\">GitRepo</link> or <link "
"xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/bundle-add\">Bundle</link> resource to a "
"specific Fleet <link "
"xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/namespaces#gitrepos-bundles-clusters-clustergroups\">workspace</link>. "
"Fleet retrieves the deployed <literal>GitRepo/Bundle</literal> and deploys "
"its contents (the <literal>K8s SUC plans</literal>) to the desired "
"cluster(s)."
msgstr ""
"Os <literal>planos do SUC do K8s</literal> são enviados a cada cluster por "
"meio da implantação de um recurso <link xl:href="
"\"https://fleet.rancher.io/gitrepo-add\">GitRepo</link> ou <link xl:href="
"\"https://fleet.rancher.io/bundle-add\">Bundle</link> em um <link xl:href="
"\"https://fleet.rancher.io/namespaces#gitrepos-bundles-clusters-"
"clustergroups\">espaço de trabalho</link> do Fleet específico. O Fleet "
"recupera o <literal>GitRepo/Bundle</literal> implantado e implanta seu "
"conteúdo (os <literal>planos do SUC do K8s</literal>) no(s) cluster(s) "
"desejado(s)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1960 l10n/source/edge.xml:2465
msgid "<literal>K8s SUC plans</literal> describe the following workflow:"
msgstr ""
"Os <literal>planos do SUC do K8s</literal> descrevem o seguinte fluxo de "
"trabalho:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1961 l10n/source/edge.xml:2466
msgid ""
"Always <link "
"xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_cordon/\">cordon</link> "
"the nodes before K8s upgrades."
msgstr ""
"Sempre use o comando <link xl:href="
"\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/generated/kubectl_cordon/\""
">cordon</link> nos nós antes dos upgrades do K8s."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1963 l10n/source/edge.xml:2468
msgid ""
"Always upgrade the <literal>control-plane</literal> nodes <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">one</emphasis> node at a time and the "
"<literal>worker</literal> nodes <emphasis role=\"strong\">two</emphasis> "
"nodes at a time."
msgstr ""
"Sempre faça upgrade dos nós do <literal>plano de controle</literal> "
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">um</emphasis> de cada vez, e dos nós do "
"<literal>worker</literal> <emphasis role=\"strong\">dois</emphasis> nós de "
"cada vez."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1964 l10n/source/edge.xml:2469
msgid ""
"Once the <literal>K8s SUC plans</literal> are deployed, the workflow looks "
"like this:"
msgstr ""
"Depois que os <literal>planos do SUC do K8s</literal> forem implantados, o "
"fluxo de trabalho terá esta aparência:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1965 l10n/source/edge.xml:2470
msgid ""
"SUC reconciles the deployed <literal>K8s SUC plans</literal> and creates a "
"<literal>Kubernetes Job</literal> on <emphasis role=\"strong\">each "
"node</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"O SUC reconcilia os <literal>planos do SUC do K8s</literal> implantados e "
"cria um <literal>Kubernetes Job</literal> em <emphasis role=\"strong\">cada "
"nó</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1966
msgid ""
"Depending on the Kubernetes distribution, the Job will create a Pod that "
"runs either the rke2-upgrade (<xref "
"linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-k8s-upgrade-components-rke2-upgrade\"/>) or "
"the k3s-upgrade (<xref "
"linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-k8s-upgrade-components-k3s-upgrade\"/>) "
"container image."
msgstr ""
"Dependendo da distribuição Kubernetes, o job cria um pod que executa a "
"imagem de contêiner do rke2-upgrade (<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-"
"k8s-upgrade-components-rke2-upgrade\"/>) ou do k3s-upgrade (<xref linkend"
"=\"management-day2-fleet-k8s-upgrade-components-k3s-upgrade\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1967 l10n/source/edge.xml:2472
msgid "The created Pod will go through the following workflow:"
msgstr "O pod criado vai percorrer o seguinte fluxo de trabalho:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1968 l10n/source/edge.xml:2473
msgid ""
"Replace the existing <literal>rke2/k3s</literal> binary on the node with the "
"one from the <literal>rke2-upgrade/k3s-upgrade</literal> image."
msgstr ""
"Substitua o binário <literal>rke2/k3s</literal> existente no nó pelo da "
"imagem <literal>rke2-upgrade/k3s-upgrade</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1969 l10n/source/edge.xml:2474
msgid "Kill the running <literal>rke2/k3s</literal> process."
msgstr "Cancele o processo do <literal>rke2/k3s</literal> em execução."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1970 l10n/source/edge.xml:2475
msgid ""
"Killing the <literal>rke2/k3s</literal> process triggers a restart, "
"launching a new process that runs the updated binary, resulting in an "
"upgraded Kubernetes distribution version."
msgstr ""
"O cancelamento do processo do <literal>rke2/k3s</literal> aciona a "
"reinicialização, o que inicia um novo processo que executa o binário "
"atualizado, resultando em uma versão atualizada da distribuição Kubernetes."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><informalfigure><mediaobject>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1972
msgid ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"fleet-day2-management-k8s-upgrade.png\" "
