#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3126
msgid "CNI Configuration"
msgstr "Configuração da CNI"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3127
msgid "Cilium"
msgstr "Cilium"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3128
msgid ""
"<literal>Cilium</literal> is the default CNI plug-in for SUSE Edge for "
"Telco.  To enable Cilium on RKE2 cluster as the default plug-in, the "
"following configurations are required in the "
"<literal>/etc/rancher/rke2/config.yaml</literal> file:"
msgstr ""
"<literal>Cilium</literal> é o plug-in de CNI padrão para o SUSE Edge for "
"Telco. Para habilitar o Cilium no cluster RKE2 como plug-in padrão, as "
"seguintes configurações são necessárias no arquivo <literal>/etc/rancher/"
"rke2/config.yaml</literal>:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3129
msgid ""
"This can also be specified with command-line arguments, that is, "
"<literal>--cni=cilium</literal> into the server line in "
"<literal>/etc/systemd/system/rke2-server</literal> file."
msgstr ""
"Também é possível especificar isso com argumentos de linha de comando, ou "
"seja, <literal>--cni=cilium</literal> na linha do servidor no arquivo "
"<literal>/etc/systemd/system/rke2-server</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3130
msgid ""
"To use the <literal>SR-IOV</literal> network operator described in the next "
"section (<xref linkend=\"option2-sriov-helm\"/>), use "
"<literal>Multus</literal> with another CNI plug-in, like "
"<literal>Cilium</literal> or <literal>Calico</literal>, as a secondary "
"plug-in."
msgstr ""
"Para usar o operador de rede <literal>SR-IOV</literal> descrito na próxima "
"seção (<xref linkend=\"option2-sriov-helm\"/>), use o <literal>Multus</"
"literal> com outro plug-in de CNI, como <literal>Cilium</literal> ou "
"<literal>Calico</literal>, como o plug-in secundário."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3131
msgid ""
"For more information about CNI plug-ins, visit <link "
"xl:href=\"https://docs.rke2.io/install/network_options\">Network "
"Options</link>."
msgstr ""
"Para obter mais informações sobre os plug-ins de CNI, visite <link xl:href="
"\"https://docs.rke2.io/install/network_options\">Network Options</link> ("
"Opções de rede)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3132
msgid "SR-IOV"
msgstr "SR-IOV"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3133
msgid ""
"SR-IOV allows a device, such as a network adapter, to separate access to its "
"resources among various <literal>PCIe</literal> hardware functions.  There "
"are different ways to deploy <literal>SR-IOV</literal>, and here, we show "
"two different options:"
msgstr ""
"O SR-IOV permite que um dispositivo, por exemplo, adaptador de rede, separe "
"o acesso a seus recursos entre várias funções de hardware <literal>PCIe</"
"literal>. Há diversas maneiras de implantar o <literal>SR-IOV</literal> e, "
"neste documento, mostramos duas opções diferentes:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3134
msgid ""
"Option 1: using the <literal>SR-IOV</literal> CNI device plug-ins and a "
"config map to configure it properly."
msgstr ""
"Opção 1: usar os plug-ins de dispositivo CNI <literal>SR-IOV</literal> e um "
"mapa de configuração para configurá-lo de maneira apropriada."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3135
msgid ""
"Option 2 (recommended): using the <literal>SR-IOV</literal> Helm chart from "
"Rancher Prime to make this deployment easy."
msgstr ""
"Opção 2 (recomendada): usar o gráfico Helm do <literal>SR-IOV</literal> do "
"Rancher Prime para facilitar a implantação."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3136
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Option 1 - Installation of SR-IOV CNI device "
"plug-ins and a config map to configure it properly</emphasis>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Opção 1 – Instalação dos plug-ins de dispositivo "
"CNI SR-IOV e um mapa de configuração para configurá-lo de maneira "
"apropriada</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3137
msgid "Prepare the config map for the device plug-in"
msgstr "Preparar o mapa de configuração para o plug-in de dispositivo"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3138
msgid ""
"Get the information to fill the config map from the <literal>lspci</literal> "
"command:"
msgstr ""
"Obtenha as informações para preencher o mapa de configuração executando o "
"comando <literal>lspci</literal>:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3139
msgid ""
"The config map consists of a <literal>JSON</literal> file that describes "
"devices using filters to discover, and creates groups for the interfaces.  "
"The key is understanding filters and groups. The filters are used to "
"discover the devices and the groups are used to create the interfaces."
msgstr ""
"O mapa de configuração consiste em um arquivo <literal>JSON</literal> que "
"descreve os dispositivos usando filtros para descobri-los e cria grupos para "
"as interfaces. O principal é entender os filtros e os grupos. Os filtros são "
"usados para descobrir os dispositivos, e os grupos para criar as interfaces."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3140
msgid "It could be possible to set filters:"
msgstr "É possível definir os filtros desta maneira:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3141
msgid "vendorID: <literal>8086</literal> (Intel)"
msgstr "vendorID: <literal>8086</literal> (Intel)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3142
msgid "deviceID: <literal>0d5c</literal> (Accelerator card)"
msgstr "deviceID: <literal>0d5c</literal> (placa aceleradora)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3143
msgid "driver: <literal>vfio-pci</literal> (driver)"
msgstr "driver: <literal>vfio-pci</literal> (driver)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3144
msgid "pfNames: <literal>p2p1</literal> (physical interface name)"
msgstr "pfNames: <literal>p2p1</literal> (nome da interface física)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3145
msgid ""
"It could be possible to also set filters to match more complex interface "
"syntax, for example:"
msgstr ""
"É possível também definir os filtros para corresponder à uma sintaxe de "
"interface mais complexa, por exemplo:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3146
msgid ""
"pfNames: <literal>[\"eth1#1,2,3,4,5,6\"]</literal> or "
"<literal>[eth1#1-6]</literal> (physical interface name)"
msgstr ""
"pfNames: <literal>[\"eth1#1,2,3,4,5,6\"]</literal> ou <literal>[eth1#1-6]</"
"literal> (nome da interface física)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3147
msgid ""
"Related to the groups, we could create a group for the "
"<literal>FEC</literal> card and another group for the "
"<literal>Intel</literal> card, even creating a prefix depending on our use "
"case:"
